Valentina, the winner of Junior Eurovision 2020, visited the French national selection for the Eurovision Song Contest where she received her Junior Eurovision trophy. She performed her song 'J'imagine' and showed her vocal strength by singing Céline Dion's 'Ne Partez Pas Sans Moi'.
We are going to France! Today it was announced that France Télévisions will be the Host Broadcaster for Junior Eurovision 2021. Read all about it here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/fra...
START VOTING NOW! You can now vote for three of your favourites! Go to https://junioreurovision.tv and VOTE!

The interval acts for Junior Eurovision have been announced! Duncan Laurence will perform together with Junior Eurovision winners Viki Gabor and Roksana Węgiel. And there is more. Read all about it here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/eve...
Arina Pehtereva will represent Belarus with her song Aliens. Get to know her: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/lea...
Say Bonjour to Valentina! Read all about her in our exclusive interview: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/bon...
We caught up with Sandra Gadelia ahead of her performance of 'You Are Not Alone' and found out lots of new information about the artist: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/san...
Susan's backstage video will follow a bit later this week. In the meanwhile, you can read all about her here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/get...
Learn what 'Beshbarmak' and 'Orama' is with Karakat, Kazakhstan's Junior Eurovision 2020 hopeful! Read more about her here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/kee...
We caught up with Chanel Monseigneur to find out more about the Maltese artist ahead of her performance of 'Chasing Sunsets': https://junioreurovision.tv/story/sit...
Ala Tracz will represent host country Poland this year. Read our interview with her here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/who...
The Russian backstage video will be re-uploaded soon. In the meanwhile, you can check out the gallery of the performance: https://junioreurovision.tv/gallery/b...
Sofia Feskova from Russia recorded her performance earlier this month. With our exclusive interview you can get to know her a bit better: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/cha...
It's time for a 'heart to heart' with Petar from Serbia. Read it here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/get...
Have you read our exclusive interview with Soleá from Spain yet? Check it out here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/mov...
The running order for the final of Junior Eurovision 2020 has been announced! Read all about it here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/thi...
UNITY from the Netherlands has recorded their performance! It's time to get to know them a bit better: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/con...

During his short visit to Warsaw, we had the opportunity to meet with Oleksandr from Ukraine. Get to know the 'Vidkryvai' (Open Up) singer before his Junior Eurovision performance on Sunday 29 November: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/che...
Will you join the #JESCWatchParty at 17:00 CET? Kick off the Junior Eurovision week by watching the amazing show from 2019 together with our 2020 stars!

It’s the moment we’ve all been waiting for! Junior Eurovision week has finally arrived and you can now follow all the preparations in the lead up to the show. What can you expect? Check it out right here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/how...
Armenia withdraws from the Junior Eurovision Song Contest 2020. Read more here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/arm...
Have you seen the Junior Eurovision stage? Check out the gallery: https://junioreurovision.tv/gallery/t...

Valentina will represent France in November! Read all about her: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/fra...
Photo by: Ahmed Bahhodh

Arina Pehtereva has been announced as the representative for Belarus at the Junior Eurovision Song Contest 2020 with her song 'Aliens'. Read all about her here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/ari...
Here are your three Junior Eurovision 2020 presenters! 🇵🇱 Read all about them: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/mee...
Soleá from Spain has released 'Palante' today. Listen to the full song here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/its...
Have you heard the final version of Oleksandr Balabanov's 'Vidkryvai'? 🇺🇦 Listen to it here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/ole...

Soleá from Spain will perform 'Palante' at the Junior Eurovision Song Contest. A 1 minute snippet of the song was released today. Listen to it here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/its...
Poland selects Alicja Tracz as their Junior Eurovision representative! Read more: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/ali...

Kazakhstan has chosen! Karakat Bashanova will represent her country in November! Read more: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/kaz...
The first news of today comes from Russia! Sofia Feskova will represent her country at the Junior Eurovision Song Contest 2020! Read more here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/rus...

An exciting day is ahead! At 12:15 CEST the music video of Germany will be released on this channel and later today, Kazakhstan, Russia and the Netherlands pick their entry. Tomorrow, it is time for Poland to choose their artist. Keep up to date with all the news as it comes in by visiting https://junioreurovision.tv !
Soleá will represent Spain at the Junior Eurovision Song Contest 2020. Read more: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/its...

The sixth participant for the 2019 Junior Eurovision Song Contest has just been announced! Eliana Gomez Blanco will represent Malta 🇲🇹 in Gliwice-Silesia later this year. Read more: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/mal...

Ukrainian broadcaster UA:PBC has chosen Sophia Ivanko as Ukraine’s participant at the 2019 Junior Eurovision Song Contest in Gliwice-Silesia, Poland. Read more here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/sof...

Kazakhstan sends Yerzhan Maksim to the 2019 Junior Eurovision Song Contest! Yerzhan is twelve years old and comes from Oral. It is the second time Kazakhstan will participate at the Junior Eurovision Song Contest. Read more here: https://junioreurovision.tv/story/kaz...

The winner of the Junior Eurovision Song Contest, Roksana Węgiel from Poland, will travel to Tel Aviv to be part of the 2019 Eurovision Song Contest. We are meeting the Polish Junior Eurovision star in Israel and will record a Q and A. Do you have any questions for Roksana? Write them down below (in English) and your question might be answered by Roksana Węgiel soon!

BLACK LIVES MATTER
To those unaware of what is going on in the US, we have been fighting injustices and racism, and enough is enough. It is unfortunate that we are still in this state, but we can definitely bring justice to those innocent lives and to the future generations. Please research on this as it affects every single one of us. It's not a race war, it's a war against racism, and we have to do what we can to help. Try to be the best ally that you can be and amplify their voices. Speak WITH them and not for them. We have to use whatever privilege and platform we have to help them be heard. We really have together for change to happen.

To my Queer people, remember that our culture was built by Black Trans People, and that is why we are able to be ourselves. We have to continue and fight for Equality and Human rights for EVERYONE!

The internet is the most powerful tool we have, and there are so many way we can help!

That's why I wanted to come here to share some ways to help the movement. Some of these ways are through signing petitions, texting and calling, donations and so much more. 

WAYS YOU CAN HELP - this links you to most of the resources and is the most current
https://blacklivesmatters.carrd.co/

IF YOU HAVE NO MONEY, STREAM THIS AND DON'T SKIP THE ADS
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bCgLa....be

Please share these informations and any new ones you come across to your friends, family and peers. And please educate them if they are unaware.
Thank you guys so much, and please stay safe!

Remember that BLACK LIVES MATTER

PLEASE READ. We create content to make you laugh and maybe escape the negativity in our world for a little while. We try to use our platform to spread love and positivity. But because of what happened to George Floyd, we can’t stay silent.
 
We’re so truly sorry to the family of Mr. Floyd and the many others who have lost their lives in similar ways. It’s heartbreaking and we’re angry about it. He shouldn’t have died that day and it’s very difficult to accept why that happened.
 
We’re lucky to have been raised in a family that does not support racism. Our parents have always modeled inclusion and taught us to love everyone. But we’re learning that it’s not enough to be non-racist, we have to be anti racist.
 
We acknowledge that we have privilege because of our skin color. We want to educate ourselves and acknowledge that we haven’t done enough in the past. We acknowledge that if we stay silent, it makes us accepting of a system that perpetuates racial inequality.
 
We’re so sorry that we haven’t done enough for the Black Lives Matter movement in the past. We’re not perfect but we want to do our best to change and do better. We want to change by standing in solidarity with all those who have suffered and been affected by racial inequality because of their skin color.
 
We are joining others in our industry for the Blackout Tuesday demonstration. We will be on mute to amplify Black voices. On Tuesday, we will not be releasing any content and disconnecting from work and connecting with our community to reflect, unite, and be a part of this change. We’ll resume posting on Wednesday.
 
#blacklivesmatter #blackouttuesday #theshowmustbepaused

I'm finally able to share this 💖
Farewell, My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic. 😭

IM STILL ALIVE. 

I'm very sorry for the abscense, it wasn't on my plans to be gone so long :( tomorrow's morning the last three episodes of the series will be finally up. There's still one episode I need to upload (Student's Councel), the TV special "Rainbow Roadtrip" and EG's last special "Holidays Unwrapped", hopefully by the end of this year or until 2020, and after that, expect me to be around with Pony Life and hopefully more pony-related content for you! 

If G5 is as good as G4 (and most importantly, if I find a nice server to download the new series), then I'll stick around 😊 

My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic was (and it'll always be) something more than special to me. Words are never enough to describe how amazing and brighter this past six years on the fandom have been to me. Waiting for a new episode every saturday, and laughing for twenty-two minutes straight in front of a monitor or my cellphone where enought to make my entire week better. I started this channel as somewhere I could find my favorite clips from the show, then it started growing and growing and suddendly I found myself uploading entire seasons with a purpouse. Now that my work will be officially done, I wanted to say thank you. Thank you guys, from the one's who've stick around since the very beggining when most of my content was about Phineas and Ferb, to all of you who've found this place over the years by clicking on your favorite moments and/or songs from My Little Pony. You gave me an opportunity to connect with people, to find my passion in animation and multimedia, to find a place where my word counts and all of your comments do too. Something as huge as this I hardly doubt it'll happen to me again, and I'm forever thankfull to God for allowing this experience on my life. 

This is not the last you'll hear of me. I'll always be here, no matter what. And if things happen to change, I want you all to know you're the best miracle I've never asked for. You're more than that, you're my family. 💖 The strongest, most amazing family I'll always count on, as much as you all count on me too💜

This isn't a goodbye. It's a goodbye 'til next time!

Love you all eternally, 
Letupita725HD★

My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic has given me more than meaningful lessons about friendship and relatable characters. I met my Best Friend throught this channel a month after I started watching ponies, took part of a fansub around the end of Season 4 where I met one of my best buds up to date, started my own episodes/movies pony blog (currently innactive after some copyright bans on the site), where I met another cool buddy who volunteered to help me with the project, and I could continue listing how I got to meet amazing dudes like Flutter525, Regular Brony, MLP Multilanguages, BronyDE and Sebas Bro (originally from Bronies Colombia), but I guess you guys got my point 😋 true is, having the opportunity to write something more than a thousand of people will read as I would never (or at least for now) dare to do in real life, is something I don't even feel I deserve. I'm nothing but a 19-year-old sharing ponies week by week. But, spending my time doing this despite my daily responsabilities is something I would never trade for anything else. I love doing this, and having a chance to speak with you guys and sharing my thoughts over here is truly amazing 😳. My Little Pony has allowed me to share as much ponies as I can over the past few years, more than that, it allowed me to learn about friendship, to learn how to maintain those frienships, and to be a better friend with whom surrounds me.

I believe many of you has your own stories, thoughts and experiences thanks to the show (which is why I started writing this preeeeeeeetty long paragraph in the first place 😆): 

What does My Little Pony: "Friendship is Magic" means to you? Has it been one of many series you started to watch by casualty and ended up being good for unexplainable reasons, or maybe it has been something that changed your life completely? What were the episodes/ movies that got you into it? I'd really love to read how you guys feel towards FiM ❤

Cinema strikes back! With Christopher Nolan's "Tenet", WarnerBros brings the first blockbuster movie to the cinemas worldwide during the ongoing pandemic. We have already seen the film and can tell you if and for whom it is worth going to the cinema. 

Please note that you should only watch the film if this can be guaranteed in your region according to health safety standards. No film is worth getting sick. 

"Tenet" is an action-espionage thriller, which takes you to numerous and varied locations in its almost 150 minutes running time. The official synopsis says: "To save the entire world from destruction, the protagonist has only one word at his disposal: Tenet. His mission leads him into a shady world of international espionage, where the laws of time do not seem to apply. Time travel? No. Inversion." 

More words should not be spoken about the plot of Tenet, the less you know, the better. You should also take the following quote from the film to heart: "Don't try to understand. Try to feel it." While other Christopher Nolan films like "Interstellar" or "Inception" are challenging, Tenet is on another level in this regard. To understand all the details of the story during the first viewing is (in our opinion) almost impossible. But that's not that important. Because the movie is still a lot of fun.

From a purely cinematic point of view, "Tenet" is an almost perfect film. The world, the characters and the action scenes are captured in captivating images. Embarrassing looking CGI-effects you will look for here in vain, since the film uses very few anyway and simply everything looks incredibly real. Only some camera cuts in dialogues between two characters are set too fast and look a bit out of place. Boring passages you will also look for in vain, the action takes the viewer from minute 1 on and so the nearly 2.5 hours of running time will fly by. 

The plot, or the complexity of the plot, will probably become the biggest point of contention among viewers and critics. The film picks up quite a bit of speed in the first 60 minutes, only to shift up a gear in the following 90 minutes. On the one hand, this is true for the plot, for the action, for the really intense and captivating moments, but on the other hand, it is also true for the explanations of the laws of time and inversion that apply to the film. While watching the film we asked ourselves again and again what was actually explained when we were already confronted with the next important scene. Then you have to decide. Do you want to be able to fully follow the plot and brood a bit more or just enjoy the following scene? (And there is really something to enjoy)

In our opinion, the characters in the film fall a bit too short, also because of the highly complex plot. All actors offer good to very good performances, such as John David Washington (as the nameless protagonist), Kenneth Branagh or Elizabeth Debicki. But Robert Pattinson stands out, who conjures up an incredibly charismatic character on the big screen.

"Tenet" is a movie that everyone with an affinity for action, espionage or thriller films should watch. It is simply fun on so many levels. Period. How much you can enjoy the movie depends on how much you can or want to follow the plot. Our rating: 8.5/10

🏳️‍🌈 Jeangu Macrooy en zijn tweelingbroer Xillan groeien op in Suriname en komen er daar allebei achter dat ze op jongens vallen. Aangekomen in Nederland besluit Jeangu dat - wanneer hij uit het vliegtuig stapt - hij op dat moment uit de kast is. In Pride Talk: We are Family praten de broers met elkaar over hun coming out, vriendschap, familie en de verschillen tussen Suriname en Nederland. 🏳️‍🌈

🏳️‍🌈 Op de dansacademie zei men tegen de mannelijke studenten 'Als jullie hier vanaf komen zijn jullie allemaal homo'. 'Echt niet', dacht Jurre Geluk toen. Maar Sacha, Jurre zijn moeder, had stiekem wel verwacht dat hij op mannen zou vallen. I would like to wish you a Happy Easter ( Happy Resurrection Day) I hope you are met with wonderful weather. I love seeing children running around with Easter baskets, collecting eggs. Just so many fond memories of my own childhood and then getting to relive that feeling all again when my son was little. Special times. For those of you that are alone and maybe feeling depression as it happens to many people during holidays for reasons of loss of a loved one through death or just a separation from family that might be due disagreements, dysfunctions and or abuse. I pray that you will do something special for yourself today! You might be the only person in your home or you might be in a situation where you are in a house full of people and yet emotionally alone. I think at some point we have all felt that and on a compassionate level "understand" it. You do have a choice!!!! You might not be able to change certain things in life but you CAN change how YOU act or react. If you can take a walk and see nature, do that, go for a stroll and breathe in the fresh air. If you are in a wheelchair, Go outside and sit and listen for the birds, feel the breeze. Even if you are in the city you can sit outside and people watch. ( that can be fun too! ) Even if you don't have kids or your single, you can still color half a dozen eggs and enjoy the process of it. Eat something you normally only have on special occasions. Say, No to housework and claim the day to be a kid and take all your coloring books down, your art supplies and create whatever you want. If you can't do any of those things I got a ton of videos you can watch and let me keep you company. From my house to your house, I love you and hope you have a wonderful weekend no matter what you do. For my Christian friends, Jesus has risen like he said he would! Praise be to God.

Stephanie Ray was born October 1, 1966, and went home to Glory December 13, 2018. We were the same age. Stephanie early retired from teaching due to medical reasons. She loved teaching. She shared many stories with me about some of her children that she taught. I meet Stephanie in the wonderful Coloring Community. We instantly hit it off. From the stories I have been hearing today after we learned of her death, She hit it off with so many people in the coloring world. I can't help but smile at the joy that she brought so many people and I know you brought her great joy. I speak for many in the coloring community when I say, We have lost a good friend. We have lost a Loyal Friend. It does hurt my heart that I didn't get to say goodbye and because of that, it all seems so surreal. I expect to see her commenting on a picture, encouraging people. She was a positive force and once again a very loyal friend. I also know that Stephanie LOVED the Lord. For us, that is where our connection was the strongest. It's in that very foundation of Faith in Jesus Christ that I know in the future I will see this precious soul again. Stephanie, Thank you for your inspiration. Thank you for making me laugh during our conversations. To all those that knew her, she was a bright light and will forever be missed. Rest In Peace but I know you and I bet you are hugging your family in Heaven and preparing for all the Christmas Joy. ( I mean it's got to be awesome right about now! Heaven is not a rest home but our eternal home and we continue to live, learn and love) Merry Christmas in Heaven sweet Sister.

Some of these tour videos can take up to 50 hours worth of time to put together, not to mention all the sacrifices I've made to buy cameras, memory cards, hard drives, annual passes and everything else associated with creating content like this.  I've just invested in more equipment for my channel and it's not cheap.  I'm not trying to sound rude, but I'm not doing this to create footage for someone to steal for their channel.  I can almost immediately identify footage that I've filmed so no matter how much you edit or alter it I WILL find out and I WILL file a DCMA take down notice.  If your YouTube channel relies on stealing footage from other YouTube channels maybe you should buy a camera and go to the parks and get your own footage or not be uploading to YouTube.  In 10+ years on YouTube and 1700+ videos I've never taken footage from another channel to use in one of my videos.  I usually spend 60-80 hours a week working to keep this going and I don't want to have to waste my time dealing with stuff like this.

We are currently looking for 2D Flash/Animate puppet animators to join our team of freelance animators. We work on a wide variety of content, mostly for youtubers across YouTube. Currently, we are working on series for both adults and children. We work hard to keep each of our animators busy with consistent ongoing work.

Must be 16+ (with guardian signature) or 18+ 

The pay is $150-400 minutes per minute of animation depending on project, skill, urgency, and difficulty. Animation rates are published and agreed to before each job. Most our animators complete between 0:30-1:30 minutes of animation per week.

With every project we do together, all the characters are already rigged with backgrounds. The rigs have a large range of body movements, facial expressions, and lip sync available. All we need is fantastic character animation, facial expressions and lip sync. We need you to bring these characters to life.

A very short animation test with one of our rigs is required. We will send you files. A contract is also required.

Must be able to complete at least 30 seconds of puppet animation per week.

*When applying, be sure to include your demo reel with rigged animation you have done.


Responsibilities and Duties
-Communicate with directors and keep them updated on progress as well as inform them of any problems that might occur.
-Work quickly on animation in order to meet deadlines.


Qualifications and Skills
-Adobe Flash and has worked with rigged characters.
-Understand basic animation principles and being able to apply these skills to our character rigs.

We are giving away 10 FREE “Am I right Lads” T-shirts.

We’ll give them to ten of our next 10,000 followers on TWITTER: https://twitter.com/smash_bits

We have 1,649 followers now. We won’t give them away till we hit 10,649 followers. Invite your friends to follow us too to help us get there faster. OH AND BY THE WAY: If a winner tell us a friend convinced them to enter, BOTH people will win T-shirts! 

(Anyone found using multiple accounts will be ineligible for this and all future giveaways.)

You can also buy the t-shirts HERE: https://crowdmade.com/collections/sma...

We will be uploading less.

For the first time in one year we have NO animation to upload Sat. 

Unlike popular YouTubers who can simply turn on the camera and finish a video in a few hours – animation takes TIME. Every cartoon takes 6-8 weeks to create and thousands of dollars each. Animators do NOT become rich and famous in today’s YouTube space. For us, it’s a work about passion. In the meantime, SmashBits Animation will be focusing most of our studio-work for clients.

Because of the recent ad-apocalypse and the demonetization of videos – we have no choice. We simply cannot invest as much as we have in the past. That means LESS videos. That means longer delays between future episodes of popular series like Undertale, Minecraft, and Hello Neighbor. 

We need to find alternative ways for all of us to invest in SmashBits content together. 

For that reason, we will poll to see what YOU want to put YOUR time and money into. 

Any other ideas? Please let me know in the comments!

-Rick

- - -
You want an Indi-Game? I’ve got 3 different games I’ve wanted to make; all of them inspired by the games we know you love (Undertale, Hello Neighbor, Minecraft, FNAF, etc): One horror game, one action RPG, and one Moba-fighter.  I’ll poll and let you pick which game before we launch a kickstarter.

You want an original animated series? We have 5 in development that we plan on trying to take to TV! Again, I’ll hold a poll and let YOU pick which one we kickstart.

You want a board game? Well, I don’t really have any ideas for that one – but I know a lot of animation companies have gotten started that way.

Merch? If you want merch let me know what you want in the comments below!

Hi guys! We hope you had a great weekend. We've got a video coming for you today! Get ready!

For years, Ellie and I have dreamed about going somewhere magical for our 10 year anniversary. Well, it’s finally time.

No laptops, no vlogging, no contracts, no business calls, and no videos on YouTube while we are away. We will see you guys soon! 

Let’s go, Ellie!! 🏝

This will always be one of my most cherished photos with Ellie. Not only is it one of our first photos together, it was taken on the first day I was able to get out of bed, put real clothes on, and walk 20 steps with a walker after my reconstructive hip surgery.

I worked so hard to surprise Ellie that day. She came over that evening to hang out with me by my hospital bed at my Grandma’s house, just like she did nearly everyday for 6 weeks.  But, little did she know, I had been working on putting on real clothes and gradually taking a couple more steps each day.

When she saw me, we both cried, slowly made our way to the backyard - step by step - and sat down to roast hot dogs and s’mores by the fire (once the room stopped spinning for me 😂).

Not only was it a big day for my recovery, but it was a big day for US as a couple. I think that’s when we truly became “Ellie + Jared”. Happy 10 year anniversary this month, Ellie.

Hey guys! Happy Monday! I hope you all had a great weekend and are looking forward to this week! It's a big one for us and we can't wait to show you what we have in store!  I wanted to give a little update in regards to the last post we made about YouTube and comments. I've found a post by YouTube explaining the details about the comments. You can read more about it here - https://support.google.com/youtube/th.... 

Basically - any channel that has kids in it OR has had kids in it will have their entire channel's comments turned off while YouTube does more work to fix the issue. As for us and future videos while this is happening, we're looking into manually reviewing each and every comment that comes through carefully approving them. Community is a HUGE reason why we do what we do and we love hearing from you! So, in the meantime while we look into managing the comments of each video, let's chat on the community tab here, Twitter, Instagram, or Facebook! I'll post links to each of our social platforms and we'd love to hear you there. I think I will even create a post for each video on the community tab to leave comments on, since it looks like everything is still good here.

Thanks for your time and understanding while YouTube sorts this out! Have a GREAT WEEK!

Good morning and happy Saturday!  You've probably noticed that all our videos have comments disabled on them (even videos without kids). This is part of a wide sweep that YouTube is doing to all family channels. I understand why. I imagine (and hope) this is temporary. (more ↓)

I hope this is a big overcorrection in order to fix a problem. I hope that once the issues are fixed in @YouTube's eyes that comments will be restored. In the mean time - let's bring discussion to Twitter and Instagram. We'll be more active there!

Also, it looks like it's only (currently) on older videos (videos uploaded before yesterday) So...I guess now is a good time to try and be the first comment before all the comments get disabled 😂

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
Under the Sea ~ Journey of The Little Mermaid

 Let's go dive beneath the waves with Ariel for an undersea adventure. This dark ride attraction is based on, Disney's The Little Mermaid. It has two locations in the Disney Parks, one opened on June 3, 2011 in California Adventure, at the Disneyland Resort, and the other one, is in the Magic Kingdom, located at the Walt Disney World Resort, which opened on December 6, 2012. You'll get to ride in a gentle moving clamshell-shaped seat through Ariel's undersea world, enjoying the music of Sebastian the Crab, then escaping the lure of Ursula the Sea Witch in this retelling of Disney's animated hit, The Little Mermaid. Some of the scenes use the original vocal actors from the film, with Jodi Benson as the voice of Ariel and Pat Carroll doing her beloved, Ursula. There are also new performances by Phillip Lawrence as Sebastian, Chris Edgerly as Scuttle, Tress MacNeille as Flotsam and Jetsam. Disney has plans for the ride to debut overseas at Tokyo's DisneySea and Hong Kong's Disneyland in the near future.

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
Splash Mountain🌊

"How do you do? Fine! A friendly greetin' / How do you do? Say it when you're meetin"
  
 Splash Mountain is a log style dark ride at Disneyland, Tokyo Disneyland, and Walt Disney World. With characters, stories, and songs based from the 1946 Disney film Song of the South. Splash Mountain was originally conceived in the summer of 1983 by Disney Imagineer Tony Baxter while stuck in rush hour traffic. He wanted to attract guests to the often-empty Bear Country land and make use of the Audio-Animatronic characters from America Sings, which was also receiving poor attendance from guests. Baxter and his team developed the concept of Zip-A-Dee River Run, which would incorporate scenes from Song of the South. The name was later changed to Splash Mountain. At the time it was being built, Splash Mountain was one of the most expensive projects created by Walt Disney Imagineering at a cost of $75 million.

Disney Attraction Series🎠
Seven Dwarfs Mine Train

"If you dig dig dig with a shovel or a pick / In a mine! In a mine! In a mine! In a mine! / Where a million diamonds shine!"

 This amazing roller coaster officially opened on May 28, 2014 and is located at Disney's Magic Kingdom theme park at the Walt Disney World Resort, in Orlando, Florida. The Shanghai Disneyland version opened on June 16, 2016. The attraction goes by so fast that some forget to see a certain someone about to knock on the dwarfs front door. The ride is worth the wait cause the queue is pretty interactive for those wanting something to do. Here's a few Disney Secrets for waiting in the queue. When you're at the spinning barrels of jewels, get everyone to spin them simultaneously and then have everyone look up for the surprise. Another cool interaction feature is a gem washing station with 12 spigots each representing a note on the chromatic scale.
 The ride features two cameras on the ride that provide videos and pictures for guests to buy through Disney's Photopass option, which it began doing on September 18, 2014. It is one of only two Walt Disney World attractions to provide videos for guests, the other being The Twilight Zone Tower of Terror at Disney's Hollywood Studios theme park.

Disney Parks Character Series 💃
We found Mulan looking elegant in Epcot

If meeting characters during your Walt Disney World vacation is important, then here are a few tips. There are four different Disney themed parks that has a plethora of characters to Meet & Greet with. Those parks are the Magic Kingdom, Epcot, Animal Kingdom and Hollywood Studios. Once you enter a park, make sure to grab an "Entertainment Times Guide" along with a park map and find your character on the list. Most likely if he/she is not on the list, they are not at that park. Always ask a Disney Cast Member for more information as they will have a times guide that they keep on them to help you out. Always always always arrive early or during Extra magic Hours for hotel park guests to get in those character lines early. Once in line you will be able to meet them, if a Cast Member cuts off the line you have missed your chance. If you got in then have fun, take a photo, get an autograph and don't forget that hug at the end!
Now for those that do utilize FastPass+, some character meet and greets have FastPass. Sometimes it's worth a FastPass if the character is very popular. So here's when early planning gets you in quicker then everyone else. With just park tickets you can select FastPass tickets up to 30 days in advance, 60 days for those who booked a Disney hotel/park vacation combo.

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
Kilimanjaro Safaris 🦁
Q: Why did the Rhino get a ticket? A: He ran through the stomp sign. 🤣😂 

Disney has created it's very own safari within the Animal Kingdom theme park, located at the Walt Disney World Resort in Orlando, Florida. It's a savanna of East Africa where animals roam free as you ride around with a tour guide in a place called, Harambe Wildlife Reserve. It was no secret that Walt Disney himself loved animals. He even wanted to use real African animals in the famous Disneyland attraction, The Jungle Cruise. So with that in mind, the Disney Imagineers created a place Walt would of been proud of.  
 This attraction takes you aboard a safari type vehicle to witness all 34 species of animals. It is 110 acres of terrain, wetlands of the Safi River valley, Ituri forest and the open bush country of the Serengeti Savanna. The many African animals on view include real live elephants, giraffes, antelopes, gazelles, crocodiles, monkeys, hippopotamuses, lions, cheetahs, hyenas, african wild dogs, warthogs, ostriches, rhinoceroses, ducks, storks, pelicans, flamingos, wildebeests, okapis and zebras. The driver will point out animals and provides information with some funny jokes as you ride along. We recommend that you go super early to see the animals waking up or get a FastPass to avoid wait times.

Cinderella Castle

 Cinderella's castle was completed 1971. The castle is 189 feet tall, as measured from the concrete bottom of the body of water. The Cinderella Castle Suite
 An exclusive hidden suite was originally built for Walt Disney and his family, though he passed away before the park was finished. The rooms sat unused and unfinished for 40 years. The suite cannot be booked or reserved. Guests need to either have won a stay through one of Disney's many contests or be invited by the company. In fact, the suite isn't even open to tours anymore.

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠 
It's a Small World

🎶"It's a world of laughter, a world of tears
It's a world of hopes and a world of fears
There's so much that we share that it's time we're aware
It's a Small World after all"🎶

 The Sherman Brothers wrote It's a Small World (after all) in the wake of the Cuban Missile Crisis which influenced the song's message of peace and brotherhood. When they first presented it to Walt Disney, he requested something more cheerful, so they sped up the tempo and sang in counterpoint. Walt was so delighted with the final result that he renamed the attraction "It's a Small World" after the Sherman Brothers' song. One of my favorite rides.
 This wonderful iconic attraction is located at several Disney Park Resorts worldwide. You can find it bringing smiles at the Disneyland Resort in California, the Walt Disney World Resort in Florida, and The Tokyo Disneyland Resort. It features 300 audio animatronic dolls in cultures costumes from around the world, singing in unity to the attraction's title song, which promotes global peace.
 Now the Disneyland Resort version, in Anaheim, California, was refurbishment and added 37 new Disney characters each in their native land. There's England hosting Alice, the White Rabbit, Peter Pan and Tinkerbell; Cinderella, Jaq, and Gus in France; Pinocchio and Jiminy Cricket in Italy; Mulan and Mushu in China; Aladdin, Jasmine and Abu in the Middle East; Simba, Pumbaa, and Timon in Africa; and South America hosting Donald Duck, Jose Carioca, and Panchito Pistoles as the Three Caballeros. The South Seas room features Ariel, Flounder, Dory, Nemo, Lilo, and Stitch. The former New Guinea Room was transformed to North America, adding Woody, Jessie, and Bullseye. Good luck finding them all when visiting Disneyland!

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
Splash Mountain🌊

"How do you do? Fine! A friendly greetin' / How do you do? Say it when you're meetin"
  
 Splash Mountain is a log style dark ride at Disneyland, Tokyo Disneyland, and Walt Disney World. With characters, stories, and songs based from the 1946 Disney film Song of the South. Splash Mountain was originally conceived in the summer of 1983 by Disney Imagineer Tony Baxter while stuck in rush hour traffic. He wanted to attract guests to the often-empty Bear Country land and make use of the Audio-Animatronic characters from America Sings, which was also receiving poor attendance from guests. Baxter and his team developed the concept of Zip-A-Dee River Run, which would incorporate scenes from Song of the South. The name was later changed to Splash Mountain. At the time it was being built, Splash Mountain was one of the most expensive projects created by Walt Disney Imagineering at a cost of $75 million.

 The Walt Disney World Resort, informally known as Walt Disney World or simply Disney World, is an entertainment complex, and is the flagship of Disney's worldwide corporate empire. The resort opened on October 1, 1971 and is the most visited vacation resort in the world, with an attendance of over 52 million annually. 
  Walt Disney died from lung cancer on December 15, 1966, before his vision of Walt Disney World was realized. His brother and business partner, Roy O. Disney, postponed his retirement to oversee construction of the resort's first phase. The original name was just Disney World, but Roy said no, and added Walt to the beginning, in remembrance of his brother.

 When visiting Black Spire Outpost, you'll see that both the Resistance and the First Order have a presence there. You will decide what side to represent when wondering around like a smuggler searching for your next adventure. Where is this smugglers paradise you ask? It's located within Disneyland Park at the Disneyland Resort in Anaheim, California, and Disney's Hollywood Studios at the Walt Disney World Resort in Orlando, Florida. 
 Once inside, you will explore the outpost and might even run into Kylo Ren and his stormtroopers, or Chewbacca and Rey.  Now, for those looking for adventure, then head straight to the attraction, Millennium Falcon: Smugglers Run. Just make sure to visit Batuu on your next visit to the Disney Parks. May the force be with you....always.

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
The Main Street vehicles

What's better than walking down Main Street U.S.A.? You could say, enjoying a morning ride down Main Street U.S.A. Either way, you should try at least one of the many vintage rides Disneyland has to offer. The Main Street vehicles are only out in the mornings and into early afternoon. After that, they exit the park due to safety concerns as the day goes on to avoid the crowds.

 One ride is the Horse-Drawn Streetcars that fill Main Street U.S.A., with sounds of horses trotting as they pull on vehicles that have been in operation since Disneyland opened in 1955. These iconic attractions have stood the test of time and will continue to entertain guests for many years to come. They're based on actual streetcars from the 1880's. 
 Another ride is called the Jitney(shown in photo). A Jitney usually implies that the vehicle carries multiple fares, and is an early version of a horseless carriage.
 Another ride is an Omnibus, a gas-powered, open-air 2-story miracle operating almost daily at the Disneyland resort. Of course riding on the 2nd story is the best view but since we were not in the front of the line to get on, a short tiny line I might add, we were given only the lower option. BUT, it turned out to be a great ride and a great view. So look for them on your next or first trip to the Disneyland Resort, in Anaheim, California.

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
The Haunted Mansion

"Welcome, foolish mortals, to the Haunted Mansion. I am your host, your... ghost host. Kindly step all the way in please and make room for everyone. There's no turning back now."
 
 Walt Disney visited the Winchester Mystery House in San Jose, California, and was captivated by the massive mansion with its stairs to nowhere, doors that opened to walls and holes, and elevators. When originally conceived in the 1950's by Walt Disney, he wanted a walk through ghost house attraction. After Walt Disney's death in December 1966, the project evolved significantly. The Disney Imagineers went hard to work then, The Haunted Mansion opened it's ghostly doors on August 9, 1969, to all who dare to enter. The public opening was announced in full page newspaper ads, attracting immediate success, by bringing record crowds and helping Disney recover from Walt's untimely death. The attraction opened at Magic Kingdom in 1971, Tokyo Disneyland in 1983, at Disneyland Paris as Phantom Manor in 1992.

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
Big Thunder Mountain
"Howdy partners! For your safety, remain seated with your hands, arms, feet, and legs inside the train and be sure to watch your kids. If any of you folks are wearin’ hats or glasses, best remove ’em, ’cause this here’s the wildest ride in the wilderness!"

 The attraction first opened at Disneyland in 1979, and the Magic Kingdom's larger version in Florida opened in 1980. Tokyo Disneyland's version opened in 1987 and Disneyland Paris opened with its version in 1992. Speeds can reach 24 to 30 miles per hour, so the G-force during the turns will pull you from one side to the next. Big Thunder Mountain Railroad was designed by Imagineer Tony Baxter and ride design engineer Bill Watkins. The concept came from Baxter's work on fellow Imagineer Marc Davis's concept for the Western River Expedition, a western-themed pavilion at the Magic Kingdom, designed to look like an enormous plateau and contain many rides, including a runaway mine train roller coaster. However, because the pavilion as a whole was deemed too expensive in light of the 1973 construction and opening of Pirates of the Caribbean, Baxter proposed severing the mine train and building it as a separate attraction.
  Here's an awesome fact about Big Thunder Mountain. The sounds of Disneyland's Big Thunder Mountain Railroad trains were recorded and used as sound effects for the mine cart chase sequence in Steven Spielberg and George Lucas' 1984 film, Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom. In the attraction queue and all around Big Thunder Mountain, you will see a century-old stamp mill, a hand-driven drill, press gears, picks, shovels and other artifacts. These objects are actual mining gear, purchased from abandoned mines in Nevada, Colorado, Minnesota and Wyoming.

 The Be Our Guest restaurant is a unique Disney Dining experience that will transport you to a world of enchantment. If you're lucky enough to book a dinner reservation you'll get to meet the master of the castle, The Beast. Breakfast & Lunch are now available as part of the castle's offerings, each reservation treated as a counter service through your Disney Dining plan. One of the magical moments during any table experience in the castle is the enchanted silverware that you can hear leaping off the tables onto the ground, as if they're trying to escape to another wing in the castle.
 Due to the popularity of Disney’s Dining Plans, it is almost impossible to just walk up and eat at a full service restaurant. If you are planning to try some of Disney’s amazing restaurants or dinner shows while you're on vacation at the Walt Disney World Resort, it is important to make Walt Disney World Advance Dining reservations online or by calling (407) WDW-DINE (939-3463). Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
Under the Sea ~ Journey of The Little Mermaid

 Let's go dive beneath the waves with Ariel for an undersea adventure. This dark ride attraction is based on, Disney's The Little Mermaid. It has two locations in the Disney Parks, one opened on June 3, 2011 in California Adventure, at the Disneyland Resort, and the other one, is in the Magic Kingdom, located at the Walt Disney World Resort, which opened on December 6, 2012. You'll get to ride in a gentle moving clamshell-shaped seat through Ariel's undersea world, enjoying the music of Sebastian the Crab, then escaping the lure of Ursula the Sea Witch in this retelling of Disney's animated hit, The Little Mermaid. Some of the scenes use the original vocal actors from the film, with Jodi Benson as the voice of Ariel and Pat Carroll doing her beloved, Ursula. There are also new performances by Phillip Lawrence as Sebastian, Chris Edgerly as Scuttle, Tress MacNeille as Flotsam and Jetsam. Disney has plans for the ride to debut overseas at Tokyo's DisneySea and Hong Kong's Disneyland in the near future.

What is #StitchDay ?
Well the story goes that on June 26, 2015, the United States Supreme Court ruled in Obergefell v. Hodges that it is unconstitutional for any of the states in America to ban gay marriage, as all U.S. citizens have the fundamental right to marry as stated by the Fourteenth Amendment to the U.S. Constitution. Because of the month and day this ruling was made on 6/26. Many fans began associating with Stitch to the date of the decision, making him its unofficial mascot. In response to this, Dean DeBlois, a former Disney story supervisor at Walt Disney Feature Animation and co-director/co-writer of Lilo & Stitch who is gay himself, drew an image of Stitch and Scrump celebrating the court's decision(Photo Below). The sketch showed Stitch holding a rainbow flag, which represents gay pride, and Scrump holding a blue flag with a yellow equality sign, representing the logo of the Human Rights Campaign. Either way, every June that comes and the 26th rolls around, everyone in the world celebrates this new holiday for two reasons. The one listed above and of course his number 626 which equals 6/26. So help us spread the stitch love fellow Disney Fans.

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
Finding Nemo Submarine Voyage
"Mine! Mine! Mine!"

 The original Disneyland attraction, Submarine Voyage, was built in 1959, and was an integral part of the Tomorrowland themed area that opened with Disneyland. It closed on September 9, 1998, and after months of speculation, the announcement was made on July 15, 2005, just two days before the 50th Anniversary of Disneyland. that Finding Nemo Submarine Voyage was officially the replacement.

 After a successful re-opening with the Nemo theme, the Disney Imagineers decided the attraction needed a long overdue makeover. The dates were planned for the overhaul, and after months of hard work, the attraction re-opened on September 27, 2014, with new scenes and a touch up of new paint for all the rocks and coral surrounding the attraction. All guests will get to see a vibrant underwater experience, that they'll never forget. Just make sure to say hello to everyone's favorite seagulls, who appear on top of a buoy in the Finding Nemo Submarine Voyage lagoon. They'll randomly flap their wings and say "Mine! Mine! Mine!"

Universal Orlando Resort Series 🌎
Hogwarts Castle
“Whether you come back by page or by the big screen, Hogwarts will always be there to welcome you home.” J.K. Rowling 

 The Wizarding World of Harry Potter is a themed area at both Universal theme parks, they include, Hogsmeade at the Islands of Adventure theme park and Diagon Alley at Universal Studios theme park, both are located at the Universal Orlando Resort, in Orlando, Florida. Hogsmeade transports Harry Potter fans to a magical snow filled wizarding village with enchanted shops for a wizard to try out some spells. Feeling hungry? Then head over to, "The Three Broomsticks", a pub/Inn based from the Harry Potter universal. The pub offers a variety of food and beverage items and features many hidden secrets from the books, namely house elves and ghosts that roam the rafters. Butterbeer is the drink of choice in the Harry Potter universe and can be purchased with a souvenir mug, which is offered as a non-alcoholic beverage and comes in both regular and frozen forms. 
 
 The two attractions that fuel Hogsmeade is, Harry Potter and the Forbidden Journey and Flight of the Hippogriff. One is a dark ride inside Hogwarts Castle and the other is right outside next to the castle. Visitors initially walk through the castle, interacting with various characters and props from the Potter movies for the forbidden journey experience. The other is Hagrid's steel roller coaster. The ride is short and goes really fast. Their both a MUST DO!

 Now, if you go to the right of the bank, you will get to see a live performance from the  musical group Celestina Warbeck and the Banshees (which was mentioned briefly by Molly Weasley in Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets). You can also catch a puppet show with a tale from the Harry Potter called, "The Tale of The Three Brothers."

Here are more things to do in Diagon Alley
-Gringotts Money Exchange is able to exchange American -currency for Wizarding bank notes.

-The Hopping Pot, and Florean Fortescue's Ice Cream Parlour, which specializes in Butterbeer-flavored ice cream.

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
Expedition Everest Legend of the Forbidden Mountain

 This steel roller coaster was built by Vekoma for Disney's Animal Kingdom theme park at the Walt Disney World Resort, located in Orlando, Florida. The ride is themed around a Yeti hiding in Mount Everest. It is listed in the 2011 Book of Guinness World Records as the most expensive roller coaster in the world, and if you include the sets and extras, its total cost was reported to be around, a $100 million dollars. It holds the record of being the tallest artificial mountain in any Disney theme park. 
 
 The attraction features a queue that starts at the office of the fictional, "Himalayan Escapes" travel agency, then progressing to a replica temple with little holy figures. Visitors will next enter a tea garden, followed by a room with equipment from a successful expedition, and then the "Yeti Museum", which contains information on the Yeti and the Yeti footprint. There are also about 8,000 artifacts brought from the Nepal trip in the museum for you to look at as you wait. The single rider line skips all of the exhibits, but is a must do, if you wanna ride it very quickly.

Taken at the Walt Disney World Resort

Kilimanjaro Safaris Series 🦁 
Q: What do you get when two giraffes collide? A: A giraffic jam. 🤣😂

 Walt Disney's love for animals was no secret, he wanted to use real African animals for the river attraction Jungle Cruise at Disneyland. This Animal Kingdom attraction is an open safari ride through the savanna of East Africa. The attraction when it debuted, had a completely different script and storyline. The current story is a short photo safari aboard a safari vehicle through the Harambe Wildlife Reserve in Harambe, East Africa. It is 800 square miles of terrain, wetlands of the Safi River valley, Ituri forest and the open bush country of the Serengeti Savanna. African animals on view include real live elephants, giraffes, antelopes, gazelles, crocodiles, monkeys, hippopotamuses, lions, cheetahs, hyenas, african wild dogs, warthogs, ostriches, rhinoceroses, ducks, storks, pelicans, flamingos, wildebeests, okapis and zebras. The driver will point out animals and provides information with some funny jokes.

 Let's visit my all time favorite place, The Mexico Pavilion in Epcot, located at the Walt Disney World Resort, in Orlando, Florida. It resembles a Mesoamerican pyramid. Visitors enter through a display of Mexican artwork, the "Animales Fantásticos" art collection. The main room is the home to a twilight lit Mexican marketplace, Plaza de los Amigos. We recommend if you're a early bird like us, then head to Epcot when it opens and head to Mexico, so you can see the opening Mexico Pavilion ceremony. Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
Grizzly River Run
Wanna see a funny Grizzly River Run Ride?
https://youtu.be/AJd3P2DfqDI

 This Disney thrill ride is the longest, tallest and fastest river rapids ride in the world and is located at Disney's California Adventure theme park at the Disneyland Resort, in Anaheim, California. The name comes from Grizzly Peak, the bear shaped mountain that the attraction was built around. It was designed by the Walt Disney Imagineering team and constructed by Intamin. The ride consists of a trip down a river in a circular rubber raft, with a platform mounted on top seating six to eight people. The raft essentially floats free in the current and is washed downstream through rapids and waves. Now one fun side note, if you are facing backwards before you fall down, prepare to get wet. 
  We love the lockers located nearby to put personal items that you don't want to get soaked. Now for those who can't ride, will have plenty of amazing places to stand as you watch your love ones go by. This ride offers SINGLE RIDER LINE!!!! lol Just ask the Disney cast member at the front of the line for a single rider voucher and then they will point the way to go.

Disney Parks Attraction Series🎠
World of Color

 It’s been nine years since the grand opening of World of Color on June 11, 2010 at Disney's California Adventure theme park, in Anaheim, California. It continues to evolve throughout its nearly nine year run, and I’m amazed by it every time I see it. The entire show cost $75 million to design, manufacture and build. The Disney Imagineers even got the huge Mickey head on the Fun Wheel to become a part of the World of Color show and even has an awesome interactive game you can play while you wait for the World of Color show on your cell phones called, "Fun Wheel Challenge."
It's easy to do, so when you're near Mickey's Fun Wheel, join the 'PierGames' Wi-Fi network to play. No need to download an app, you can play the game right in your browser.
  Here are some awesome tips to enjoy World of Color while there. The FastPass is first-come, first-served tickets to same day World of Color shows. The FastPass machines are near The Little Memaid Ariel's Undersea Adventure. Another veiwing option is a dinner package. They can be found at two different California Adventure restaurants, one is called Carthay Circle Restaurant and the other is, Wine Country Trattoria Restaurant. The dinner packages includes complimentary tickets to the Reserved Viewing section of World of Color. We recommend doing one of the dining packages.

Disney Parks Authentic Original Merchandise Series🛍

 Top your day at The Happiest Place on Earth with the purchase of an awesome Pandora souvenir from Windtraders, located in the Pandora theme area. This collection is very detailed and colorful, and includes merchandise that looks out of this world. You can even own your very own Pandora banshee, exclusively at Walt Disney World's Animal Kingdom theme park, in Orlando, Florida. 
 
 Now some of the Disney Parks merchandise we showcase, may still be available to purchase or the item is retired, but no worries, you maybe able to find the items online though a seller. Disney uses the “Authentic Original” logo to identify those as, items that are made and sold exclusively at Disney Parks. Items with this logo won’t be found at local Disney Stores, or at other locations that carry Disney merchandise beyond Disney Parks (one exception is the Disney Parks online store or a local discount Disney outlet store). 
Now if you are away from the Disney Parks but may be interested in merchandise, you can find them with the launch of the Shop Disney Parks mobile app. Shop Disney Parks app lets you shop your way, by making it easy and convenient to find your favorite Walt Disney World Resort authentic products. The app offers access to thousands of products, including some of the newest arrivals created especially for Disney Parks. New products will be added weekly. The app also provides delivery options which let you ship directly to your home. 
  We recommend looking for your item first on the Shop Disney Parks app before contacting the Guest Services team. These cast members can help you obtain items at Disneyland Resort, Walt Disney World Resort, and Aulani, a Disney Resort & Spa in Ko Olina, Hawai`i. 
 There are two ways to order Disney Parks merchandise when your far away from the parks, and that's the online shop at www.shopdisney.com or download the Shop Disney Parks mobile app on your smartphone.

What is Star Wars Day?
Star Wars Day, May 4, celebrates Star Wars, which was created by George Lucas. The celebration is felt across the entire world. The date was chosen for the easy pun on the catchphrase, "May the Force be with you" as "May the Fourth be with you". Even though the holiday was not actually created or declared by Lucasfilm, many Star Wars fans across the world have chosen to celebrate the holiday. Since 2013, The Walt Disney Company has officially celebrated the holiday with several Star Wars events at The Disneyland Resort and at the Walt Disney World Resort. The following day, May 5, has come to be known as "Revenge of the Fifth", a play on Star Wars: Episode III, Revenge of the Sith. On this day, fans join the "Dark Side" by celebrating the Sith Lords from the Star Wars series.

Stitch signing our autograph book while we dine

 One of the best kept Disney secrets is, "Best Friends Breakfast featuring Lilo & Stitch" at The Polynesian Village Resort Disney Character Dining experience. With breakfast selections including scrambled eggs, Island-style fried potatoes, Hawaiian pork sausages, smoked bacon and a variety of fresh fruits and breads, sounds good? Then make sure to make advance reservations, which is highly recommended and can be made up to 180 days prior to your visit. Ask if you can get a table near a window to see a view of the Magic Kingdom while enjoying your breakfast. Your meal will keep coming till you're stuffed. The Polynesian's tropical setting is the perfect match for Lilo, Stitch and their friends. A PhotoPass photographer will come with the characters while they visit your table. The Kids will love the little dance party they do during the breakfast. It's a MUST DO!

"Partners" is a statue created by Disney Imagineer and animator Blaine Gibson for Disneyland. It has been replicated in other Disney parks, to Disney studios, and you can even find it in merchandising when visiting the Disney parks. Here, we find the statue on a beautiful day, with the sun shining bright on Walt Disney and Mickey Mouse as they greet the many guests who enter the park everyday. Partners indeed. When you're there, the outside world doesn't exist. It's funny, cause when I come back from long trips, I find out what I missed in the news and be like, "That happened?" 😂 Download for your phone or computer for an awesome wallpaper for free.

Mickey's Royal Friendship Faire Series

 You are cordially invited to the brand new castle stage show playing daily in the Magic Kingdom, at the Walt Disney World Resort, in Orlando, Florida. Mickey's Royal Friendship Faire debuted on June 17, 2016, replacing the beloved Dream Along with Mickey show. This new magical tale has Mickey and his friends venturing far and wide to invite more Disney friends from other lands to join in their celebration. From the Land of the Bewitching Bayous, Goofy has invited Tiana, Naveen and Louis to add a little spice of New Orleans jazz to the party. From the Land of the Enchanted Woods, Donald Duck brings some new friends he met at the Snuggly Duckling, and Daisy introduces us to her special guests, Rapunzel and Flynn Rider. Finally, Mickey shares a surprise with Minnie, as he has traveled to the Land of the Mystic Mountains to invite Olaf, Anna and Elsa, who contributes a blast of her icy magic. Featuring songs from Disney’s classics like “Princess and the Frog,” “Tangled” and “Frozen.” The show runs about 15- 20 minutes.

Whether it's Marvel or DC, the topic of superheroes has been my favorite thing for my whole life. When I was 11 years old, my friends and I had a huge idea for a Batman parody movie we wanted to make but we had no access to a video camera. When my Aunt got one, the first thing I did was make a Batman mask and cape out of garbage bags and make my own Batman movie. The fact that I get to make these hilarious superhero videos every week for people all over the world is literally my dream come true! Now I'm going to take it to the next level. When we do our "The Batman" trailer parody you're going to see an evolution in our style. Then get ready for a 20-minute version of the comics series "The Superior Spider-Man" coming later this fall. And then our attention will turn to a big feature film project that's been in the works for 2 years! I can't wait to tell you more about it! So stay subscribed, and consider becoming a channel member to support these projects! And following the show on Instagram - @the.sean.ward.show - for awesome new pics every single day!

Our good friend Greg, mixologist at Bambou in Paris came up with the recipe for the #LoneDrinker cocktail:
In a mixer/blender, put:
6 cl of fresh cucumber juice.
1 cl of cane sugar.                    
A few blackberries.  
Mix, then pour in a cocktail shaker with ice cubes and 4cl of Vodka, shake well.
Pour in the glass, top up with Ginger beer and serve with a petite carrot!
(For a virgin version of this cocktail, just leave the vodka out)

Привет мои хорошие у меня для вас одновременно хорошие и плохие новости. Фанаты Ледибаг и Супер Кот ждёте продолжения сериала Сумерки с Маринетт и Адрианом?! 💖
Я создала две серии по фильму и конечно же работаю над продолжением, которое вы уже совсем скоро увидите (кадр из 3 части) Но есть небольшие изменения мои предыдущие части были по 10 минут каждая и ютуб их воспринял как целый мультфильм. 🙃
Что в этом плохого? Из-за этого вы уже не можете писать комментарии под видео к второй части, тоже самое ждёт и первую часть.😭 А так же я не могу их рекламировать и распространять. Ютуб не распознал мой монтаж и решил, что я украла целый мультик в 10 мин. Теперь чтобы избежать всех проблем с каналом я делаю следующее. Мне пришлось поделить эти видео по 3-4 минуты максимум. Завтра выйдет видео в первые 3 минуты от 1 части Сумерки и так далее каждую неделю. После того как выйдут все части которые вы видели сразу начнут выходить новые, которые я уже сделала. Иначе ютуб в любой момент удалит первые две части, и вы их больше никогда не уведите. 
Надеюсь на ваше понимание  ✨

To whomever reads this,

I decided to take my videos down as I do not want to be notorious for my inappropriate content of future generations, more-so the teen generations and older, to view my taken down videos. To be honest I made both of my published videos in the 7th grade as a joke, thinking it would never attract media attention. In my freshmen year, It had "circled back" to a popular news source I will not list, reaching over 1 mil views. It was at that point I realized what I've done. As much as I thought reaching a million views was cool, I decided to avoid future notoriety of myself by removing my videos. I realized my use of "certain" words in these videos and old memes were considered a little "excessive." (It was my 7th grade nature!) I know future YouTubers may try to bring my videos back, I will try my best to remove them. If you could try helping remove them, you can link this post to Google or YouTube or whatever. 
Thank you!

-DJTwirlz

A quick update. There has been a lot of Babylon 5/Crusade uploads the last few months. Some viewers will be sad and others happy to note that the last footage for Babylon 5 & Crusade has been uploaded.

Babylon 5/Crusade was the largest uploaded footage i have done so far for a TV Series. I made some mistakes in cutting parts of it into smaller chunks, which in hindsight i regret. I have taken criticism to heart and in future will space out and balance uploads in more manageable chunks. 

The next footage that is not Babylon 5 related has already been uploaded and will be going live in the next week. Sneak peak soon after you receive this post.

🎨Art by Yen

⭐Happy New Year everyone! ⭐
2020 was absolutely crazy for everyone, I hope you are all good and staying as healthy as possible! I just wanted to say that you guys made our 2020 absolutely wonderful! I’m super happy you guys are absolutely loving the new style of content I’ve adapted in 2020! To be honest it’s been super fun to make as I can get as crazy as I want during it which is so mentally relaxing as a creator to make something you’re happy and proud to make while having fun with everyone enjoying it! (Plus in 2020 that was super needed!) We’ve gained 2.8 million subscribers in just 2020 alone, which is our highest year yet for subs! So welcome all you new lovelies, I hope you will grow with me as much as you enjoy! 💜

⭐I wanted to give an update on my prior RP content. LOTS OF TEXT!⭐
Back in 2019 I was nearing the end of my weekly roleplay era. Before 2020 my channel was heavily dependent on roleplays (or story-type content) while Jason and I enjoyed making RP’s and we loved it just as well, it was impossibly difficult to keep up at the rate we had been posting for years. The production of weekly RP’s at the quality we aimed for was incredibly stressful, once COVID hit we couldn’t have our work place anymore and had to send everyone home. Making an RP remotely and expecting it to be posted every week without error and greater amounts of stress is impossible with our quality. On top of that RP’s were not making as many views as they needed to fund them. So after 4 years of making that content we decided it was in our best interest for our mental health/family that we not rely on RPs as much as our main content. YouTube is our job, it’s what we do to make a living and pay for everyone who works for us, it’s a fun job! But at the end of the day we have to make decisions that are in our best interest. 

To be honest I was really getting upset with how often demands had come in for me to post faster, it caused me to rush stories that I didn’t want to rush but had to. It also caused me to set dates for releases I didn’t know if we could make. Diaries Rebirth was my chance to not rush and when I felt like I was rushed I stopped it because I no longer wanted to feel rushed on a story. I hope you guys can understand that.

With that being said, Jason and I are not stopping our story telling, we still have stories to tell, but we’re not about posting them on a tight schedule as we did for many years anymore. That’s incredibly draining and not good for anyone’s well-being. So instead we’re going to take our time making RP’s. There will no longer be a set date on when anything is airing, instead we want to produce the whole RP at our own pace before even beginning to announce anything. Again this is a decision that helps me feel better as a person/creator and puts me at less stress to make something not rushed, so I hope you guys can understand this stand I am taking. I also want to find ways to make my RP’s more entertaining so this gives me the time to take that time.

Oh! If you are concerned about me right now don’t worry! I’m perfectly fine! I’m still able to post daily, my current daily content is very fun and less stressful because I can get as crazy with it as I like, which is very relaxing! (Jason as well!) 

So here’s a small TL;DR on plans:
1.) No set dates/times on RP’s anymore, they’ll come out as we want them to. Please don’t expect set dates/times anymore, as we’ll only post set dates when we have things in a state we want them. Which could be many days/months/whenever or so.
2.) Whenever it is we choose to post series RP’s they will not be on this channel. They will be on my other channel “Aphmau Stories” (unless something changes).
3.) We’re also looking to expand into different types of storytelling mediums (like animation). Again not set in stone but a fun idea!  
4.) I want to conclude MyStreet Season 7 at some point, but I’m not sure how yet and that will take a long while to decide what I want to do. 

Thank you guys so much for supporting me through everything. If you can wait for me or not is your choice, but it’s a decision that (cannot stress this enough) really helps me as a creator.
Some of you have been with me for many years, we’ve been making content for 8 years now and a lot of you have grown up. You probably look at me differently now, I won’t be that star that shines to you forever, but it makes me happy that in some way I was a part of a chapter in your life and could put a smile on your face. I’ll always be here making content, if you ever wanna come see me again, I’ll be here waiting, just make sure you’re happy 💜
Love, AphMom 💜

Hey y’all! This is gonna be a bit of a serious post - I wanted to talk about PDD and the FUTURE! Oooh scary I know! But it’s something super important that I want to be transparent with you guys about. I’m sure for some of you guys PDD seemed like it ended abruptly, and you’re not wrong to feel that way because IT DID end abruptly. Originally there were more episodes planned, however due to analytics showing a decline of interest it became difficult to produce without losing a LOT on it, both in manpower and money. RP’s at the rate and quality I post them, take a LOT of funds to produce, which is why your support on vids is so important and very much appreciated! This is true for any YouTuber’s channel when it comes to series. Being a content creator costs time and helping in support is the best way to help fund us. Support can be shown by views/likes/comments/subs/check out merch/patreon/etc. - which is why you will see creators asking you to participate in those things. All those things HELP a lot and keep creators able to keep doing what they do [so thank you guys!]
That being said PDD had to be cut short, tho PDD isn’t the only series I’ve had that had to be cut short due to a loss of interest, there are a small few series that had the same fate in the past – however NOT ALL SERIES are ended because of a lack of viewership, there are series I just wanted to do and did just because I wanted to. HOWEVER with YouTube having a LOT of changes coming in 2020 I may not have the luxury of doing that anymore.
I’m sure by now a ton of you guys have heard about COPPA [I wanted to make a vid on this on my vlog channel, may still but for now not sure] I’ve been aware of it, especially as a parent it’s been a concern of mine for a while. It’s a law that’s been in place since 1998 and it’s just now starting to affect the YT platform. I’ve marked my channel as not for kids as a lot of my subject matter aims 13+ since my series tends to focus a lot on romance and adult jokes. There are plenty of YT vids on COPPA however NO ONE KNOWS WHAT IS GONNA HAPPEN COME JAN. 1st 2020 it’s all majority speculation, which is why I haven’t spoken about it until now. I don’t want you guys to fear what will happen to me when I don’t even know what’s gonna happen to me. For now I’m gonna play it by ear and hope for the best. But don’t worry about me, if anything happens it’s gonna be hard but we’ll find a way. I’ll try to be as open with you guys about the future as I can (which is what I’m trying to do here). What I can speculate tho is that a lot of things will change in the algorithm (since changes are already starting to take effect) and I will be put in a tough position where series will have to take different turns.
Please believe me when I say I love you all dearly, you guys helped me through a lot and I sincerely love what I do! But real truth here, it is exhausting to be on a platform that constantly changes without communication and you have to adhere to or else you die. As YouTubers there are things we are just left guessing on how to make things work for our channel. So please understand changes coming up may be bumpy, but they’ll be done the way I want to do them. To all of you who support me… I love you… thank you 💜
AGAIN! I’ll see if I can get a vlog up on my vlog channel, but again it’s so hectic with the holidays @~@; I’ll try to keep things over text as best I can. Know that there are many factors in every decision and not everything is simply black and white (tho communication from YT or the FTC would be appreciated so creators aren’t left guessing 😢)
For now I don't have any direct ways to help as I've already submitted my thoughts to the FTC, however if you want to help, not only me but the creators you care about, be sure to watch our vids, like, and subscribe. When I know of more ways to help, I'll let you guys know! Again, thank you guys so much 💜

TL;DR: Murder is now called Angels VS Demons. Diaries is coming out at my own pace for my own sanity, MID iin the mean time to make up for that is coming out twice a week.
1.) I mentioned this in a stream, but I wanted to make sure you guys knew that I’m currently taking MCD:R at my own pace. Which means vids for Diaries will come out when I have them ready. I was feeling like I was rushing to meet a schedule and while that was my aim, it took a toll on me and with MCD I just want to be happy with the remake. So I hope you guys can understand, but I do plan on continuing it, just at a slow pace. To make up for it MID has been releasing twice a week.
2.) Some of you may have noticed that this recent Minecraft Murder was renamed and re-themed to “Angels VS Demons”. If you haven’t noticed… well now you do, haha! But there’s a reason for that. Some of you are probably aware that a lot of things with YouTube's algorithms are changing, that being said the word “Murder” is just in general a bad term to use for my channel, so we had to revamp the game in order to make it acceptable by the algorithm. Unfortunately it’s something a lot of YouTuber's are going through right now where we have to change certain aspects of the channel in order to keep doing what we’re doing – that being said you may see a few other things change, but I plan to keep true to my content and only making what I am happy putting out. I don’t mind replacing words with others honestly as I already do that as a mum XD So yes, if you see stuff like that, know it’s because YouTube is going through a lot of system changes. 

So that’s pretty much it for this post in terms of updates! I am so appreciative of you guys being so supportive and allowing me to take my time with certain things. It helps so much 💜

Happy New Year from us SkillTwins to you! 😁😎💥🎉
We've listed our biggest achievements during 2017.🏆
We want to give a big thank you to our wonderful team, family, fans and to everyone that supports us. 
You mean so much to us. 🙏
Here are some of our highlights during 2017:
🏆 We did our first ever ''SkillTwins Panna Tour'' where we have several events around the world meeting our fans and skilling with them.
🏆 We released our 2:nd mobile game called ''SkillTwins Football Game 2'' where both games now have over 10 million downloads in total world wide.
🏆We did our first ever commercial together with EA Sports and the game FIFA.
🏆 We signed our first ever book deal with ''Bonnier Carlsen'' where we are telling our inspirational story - Stay tuned for more...
🏆 We signed our first ever car company deal with "Volkswagen" - 2018, be ready!
🏆 We signed with the biggest sport network in the world called ”TheWhistle Sports” that we've some awesome plans with...
🏆 We won the best ''Social Media Marketers'' in our hometown.
🏆 We were the front cover of different sport magazines.
🏆 We were at one point the world's fastest growing Facebook page out of all pages on Facebook.
🏆 We met up and created videos with some amazing artists that we admire such as: @marcusandmartinus & @niallhoran!
🏆 We won the ''Stockholm Soccer Showdown Game" where we scored 4 goals having the legendary football player ''Henrik Larsson'' as a coach.
🏆 We met up with a person that we admire and look up to. The great entrepreneur and social media guru: Mr. @GaryVee - He even named us in his presentation!
🏆 We meet the Prince of Sweden, Prince Daniel. Turns out that he has seen our videos which was very inspirational.
🏆 We appeared live on one of Sweden's biggest TV shows called ''Bingolotto''. It has over a million viewers on New Years Eve! We was 2 of the head guests at the program.
🏆 We had several Freestyle Live shows that we enjoyed a lot!
And we've some crazy announcements coming 2018... Let's do this - It's ShowTime! 🏆

An important message for everyone
Please stay safe.

Few weeks back my mummy and papa tested positive for covid-19.
Not only mummy papa but my uncle,aunt, my nephew Adi (yes that little kid) & even my cousin brothers from ACV team jashan and tanish tested positive for corona

We isolated Mummy, papa & adi in their rooms and took extreme care of them
The first 2 days hit me and muski hard 
We were anxious and very scared, the thought of it sent shivers down our spine
We were too emotional
Hearing about it since last 4 months in news and seeing it up close and personal are 2 very different aspects of coronavirus.
We are so lucky and blessed that my family did not face severe consequences, CANT EVEN IMAGINE WHAT POOR PEOPLE MUST BE GOING THROUGH.
