Hey Everyone!  So, I've been taking quite a bit of time to work on a homebrew superhero game that's based on 5e (but not 5e compatible! I call it a 'hacked 5e') If you're curious to see what I've been working on, up sharing some of the files up at the site:  https://puffinsite.wixsite.com/website  which is a site I'm really only using to share these files. The game is still very VERY ROUGH, ugly, and MILES away from being in a playable state, particularly the enemies section is VERY sparse. But if you want to look it over, you're welcome to. Enjoy! If you do try to run it, be warned, there's probably going to be many rules questions that the rules don't have answers for. On the site there's: the base rules, pregens, blank character sheet, and some sample enemies.

Hey guys!

We wanted to thank everyone for their continued support! As a friendly reminder, please do not bully anyone on YT (or anywhere else) if they post a reupload or react video...or for any other reason. We appreciate that you guys care so much about our work, but we also do not want anyone to feel overwhelmed with hate comments - there is a real person on the other side of that screen and, at the end of the day, their emotional well-being is much more important than any video. 

Anyone who has been on the internet for a long time has probably lost their cool and/or said/done hurtful things at some point, we are no exception, but that doesn't mean we cannot all move forward and try to make the internet a less hateful place. 

If you want to report a video, please email us at askterminalmontage@gmail.com. Do not harass anyone. When we have time, we can look at the video and make a decision on whether or not to claim it.   

Again, we cannot thank you guys enough for everything this channel has become. We could not have done it without you and all the amazing talented people who have been a part of our videos!

Hi Everyone,


We hope you are all still staying safe and well!


It looks like many places around the world are slowly easing up on the lock-downs. While taking proper pre-cautions, we're excited to start seeing a glimpse of "normal" life again. Meanwhile, we remain as committed as always to make inspirational, entertaining and educational content for you.


As you may have seen in some of our videos, we've been working with UNESCO (United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization) on projects to help them with their mission to build peace through international cooperation in education, the sciences and culture. We strongly believe in the importance of their mission and are excited to help spread the word on their efforts.


Recently we worked with them on a video about the "Rule of Law". It might sounds like a very basic principle, but yet the world still has a long way to go. It is the sad truth that many injustices take place all around the world on a daily basis. UNESCO partners with UNODC to improve education on the rule of law, developing interactive handbooks for schools and guidance for policy-makers. They aim to bridge the gap between education and justice and support Sustainable Development Goals 4 and 16 to make the world a better place.


We hope you like the video and that it gives you perspective on the importance of the rule of law.

An Inhaler Almost Killed Me. I was only 8 years old. I was an energetic little girl that is always active and happy. Until my dad noticed that I began wheezing. So he got me an inhaler. At first I would take a pump or two just when I was wheezing. But soon, I started taking more pumps. I didn't think anything bad would happen. My stomach would hurt at some times, but I just thought they were common stomach aches. I was wrong. One day, a little before Thanksgiving, I was at my grandpa's furniture store, and I was in pain. After I got home I lied in bed crying until I began vomiting the lunch I ate that day. My parents rushed me to the doctor. My heart was beating so fast, I had to get a shot. At the time, I was terrified of needles and as they gave me the injection, I started crying loudly. After that, they called an ambulance and I was rushed to a hospital. The nurses were going to give me one more shot and an I.V. and I was so scared. Back then, before I got sick, there was this this game I really wanted. My dad said that if I didn't freak out while getting my shots, he would get the game for me. The game was called Super Mario Galaxy. And I tried not to scream or cry. Mom arrived at the hospital and after getting what I needed, I was put into another room. I was hooked up to machines, and didn't understand what was happening. I told my parents I wanted to go home now. Dad slept next to my bed as I fell asleep. The next day, the doctors told me that I had pneumonia. I stayed int he hospital for a few days but on my last day at the hospital, I was sent home in a wheelchair. I was given medicine for at least a month. I feel a lot better now, but I would have to accept that I would permanently have asthma. I am now thirteen and I still suffer with breathing problems. But now I use an inhaler one pump at a time to avoid another problem like that again.

My Mom Hates Me Because of My Body. 
My mum was always skinny. A small chest, flat stomach, thigh gap. She was so happy when my older sister turned out the same way. She praised her for being a size 6 aged 15. Me, on the other hand, I wasn't the same build. Yes, I was slim, but I wasn't like my sister and mother. My chest was the same size as my sister when she was two years older, my stomach wasn't completely flat, but it was pretty flat, and I had a smaller thigh gap than my sister. My mum started to get angry when I was the same size in clothing as my sister, despite the fact she was 3 years older. "You're too big. You need to be smaller" she'd always say. After that, she treated me differently. She didn't allow me to eat anything between meals and got really mad if I did. My food was bland: No sugar, no carbs, no flavor. Nothing that would make me 'bigger'. After time, I started to shrink. Aged 16, I had gone down to a size 4- sometimes needing the children's section. My body couldn't cope with my food intake- I contracted anorexia, found it hard to use the toilet, even found my monthlies were getting shorter. But my mum didn't care, as long as I was thin. I'm trying to improve my health now. I have a job, so I'm saving up for a flat to rent. And I have a boyfriend, who is willing to support me and try to help me be healthy again. The minute I can get out, I'm going to sort my food regime out: I won't let my mother starve me. I want to be slim, but not unhealthily slim. And I WON'T let my mother treat me like this anymore.

I had to save my baby sister from our father. One day, when I was around 6, I was at my biological father's house and this day was the worst day of my life. He couldn't figure out why my half-sister of 3 months was crying and it drove him insane. He picked her up by the leg and threw her against the wall. She bounced off of the wall into her wooden crib, and was hurt pretty bad. I then went into the room and grabbed my little sister and waited for my step mom to get home from work. My step mom asked me what happened and I told her everything. So she called the police. I ended up having to go to court to tell the judge what happened. My father and another family member on my father's side accused me of lying because I'm a 6 year old. Then my father was imprisoned for a long time. I am now 16 years old and in the 11th grade in high school. I have lived without my biological father for 10 years now because I'm not allowed to have any contact with him until I am 18 years of age - according to the court. Though he still made my life horrible for a little while. My mom and step dad are still together, I look at my step father as my real father because he's taken care of me since before my biological father went to prison. I suffer from depression and PTSD, and anxiety. But I'm doing good, and I have great grades in school and only two years left in school. I will walk across that stage, with or without him. I will succeed in life, with or without him. Not having my father in my life is hard even till this day, but he isn't going to stop me from doing anything just because he isn't in my life. It's all thanks to my mom and stepfather cheering me on and supporting me. I am overcoming everything that has happened but I’m doing good. Very good.

My Husband Left Us for a Younger Woman. It was Monday, he finally had the night off for us to spend together as a family. I come home, he’s cleaning. Loading the dishwasher and cleaning out the fridge. I sit on the couch and snuggle with our two year old boy when I realize he’s acting strange. “Are you okay? What’s wrong?” I ask him. “We have to talk about something. Something happened today that will effect our marriage.”....”what?” I ask in a scared and worried tone. “What do you think?” He says.”did you sleep with someone?...” I begin to cry. “Yes..” he says, ashamed. “ who?”...”who do you think?” It was a girl from his job. Someone he worked with, and he’s actually her superior at his job. He had been unhappy in our marriage for a year unbeknownst to me. My husband works constantly and spends more time at his job than he does with us. He loves his job. He’s a correctional officer. What he did in sleeping with this girl was his easy way out. His escape from me without having to face or confront our problems. Because they stemmed from him working so much. And he doesn’t want to give that up even still. I never imagined that this man would hurt me this way. I begged him to make it work, to love me, to keep our family together. I lost my dignity and respect for myself. I am no one’s option or second choice. I love that man even still and I’m not even at a place yet where I can say I’ve moved on but every passing second becomes a little bit easier.

"I'm just a normal schoolgirl living in Hong Kong. Recently, there had been a lot of things happening around me and new things every single day. There are a series of anti-governmental protests going around the city. Soon enough, I'd found out that we cannot simply "hold no stance." My classmates just keep asking me "who do you support?" or "what do you think about the recent news?"  Seeing protesters and police or other people fighting just because of their difference makes me feel sad and frustrated. Why can't the government just accept their people or try to make a deal with them? Although they don't have a common leader, they have a common thought or idea! And they can always go to meet some protesters or citizens and talk? You can argue that they had tried. I have to admit, yes, they had tried, but it is just the wrong way! Yes the protesters vandalize, but if the government actually listens to them, it won't happen! I am just so frustrated. At this point, I have many questions. Why can't the government just listen to their people? Why are there such people who risk the whole city's fate just to keep your "good image" in front of the central government? Can't you just listen to your people? Do you know how much people cry themselves to sleep every night just because of this? Yes, a lot of police are hurt, a lot of people who "like the government" are hurt. But, think about this, the majority of your people can also decide the fate of your rule. Also, there are plenty of other people that are hurt both physically and mentally. There have been dozens of people that committed suicide, or thought of doing it, or was actually, purposefully or accidentally killed in the events! I really cannot hold this back anymore, I'm just 13 and as an introvert, I don't really like to express myself verbally but I just felt so angry and sad and I am just about to explode because of this. I really need to express myself and my views."

“For years I suffered [with Social Anxiety] in silence. I felt so embarrassed and ashamed that I didn’t tell anyone or seek help. I was raised to believe it was weak to talk about feelings. When I did try to tell people, I felt they didn’t understand me or what I was going through. I was told things like “harden up” and “who cares what others think?” I have since come to realize that admitting you need help and talking about your feelings is one of the bravest things you can do.

Asking for help is the first step to change: If you act like everything’s all right when it’s not, how do you expect anyone to be able to help you? Statistics show that most people suffer in silence for around 10 years before seeking help with social anxiety. That is crazy because this condition is treatable. My life changed when I sought help. I went to see psychologists and I met a former social anxiety sufferer who, through a lot of effort on his part, managed to persuade me that social anxiety was not a life sentence. Once I believed that I could overcome social anxiety, everything changed for me.

The psychologists taught me to stop calling myself hurtful names like loser, ugly, and weird. They taught me to accept myself for all of who I am, good points and bad. They taught me that nobody's perfect, but that’s OK because I don’t need to be perfect or never appear awkward for others to like and accept me.

Instead of always looking for others to approve of who I am, they taught me to look for my own feelings of self-worth and validation. When that happened, all of a sudden what other people thought of me didn’t seem to matter that much anymore. I became more concerned with how I felt about me.”
.
.

Hi I have a super rare neurological disorder called VS or Visual snow or Visual static. It's such a rare syndrome that it took me 19 years to discover it, I thought I saw the world like everyone else around me but I was sadly wrong. Can you believe that I thought it was perfectly normal to see static? I remember as a child I would go to my mother and ask, "what are those tiny flickering lights I see?" My mom would give me a confused look and say, "OH those are called floaters sweetie, that's normal." So, that's pretty much why I thought it was normal. BUT NOOO it wasn't floaters, floaters are the tiny see-through squiggly shapes you see if you stare at something bright over a long period of time. I see white, black, red, grey tiny dots blinking in-and-out, covering my whole vision, it's constantly happening, 24 hours a day, I can't escape it. It gets worse when I close my eyes or if I'm in a dark room. In complete darkness I see a kaleidoscope of dancing static. I don't know what the color 'black' looks like, and I've never seen darkness before. All I see is dancing colors moving like an old TV static. I hate it. What's worse is, this is just one of my symptoms. People with VS suffer from tinnitus, palinopsia, Starburst effect, or other visual effects such as glare, halos, odd colors and shapes, or double vision (diplopia), depression, anxiety and many more. As an artist this is a huge obstacle that I can never escape, there is no cure, no treatment. I felt like it's all in my head, but it's not. I was online and found an organization called Visual Snow Initiative. They're the only people in this world who are researching this rare disease. They found out that VS has nothing to do with the eyeball but it's the processing of the Cortex of the brain that's screwing up, like it's not functioning right. SO I'M writing this because this rare disease needs to be known!!! I'm sure so many people are out there like me, I was confused and lost, BUT you're not alone. This is a real illness and you're not crazy!!!"

"Depression is kinda like drowning. At first, you're still bobbing up and down, still having those quick moments to catch your breathe. You try to wave your arms around to show people you need help but after a while of no one noticing, you decide to reserve that energy just to try to survive, to keep your head above the toxic water. You hold your breath and tell yourself that none of these negative thoughts are true and to not let it completely consume you and you're successful for a while - still catching some air every now and then. But after a while, after you struggle and struggle, you start to run out of energy. And then you slip and let a thought get through. You're weak. After a while, more of them get to you. You try to hold your breathe but you just can't hold it anymore. And then your air runs out, your energy is completely gone and you can do nothing but succumb and just let it in. And that's when they take over your mind completely. Flooding all of your thoughts. Regret. Shame. Anxiety. Guilt. Resentment. Mistakes. Unsaid words. Insults. Criticism. Pain. Hate. Anger. Envy. Grief. Anguish. They all come for you in one go. You can't do anything other than just let go and slip under the weight of them all. Until everything is a blur and all you can see is the tiny little circle of light that's moving farther and farther away from you. You look over your life. You don't see the good. You don't see the positive. You don't see the light. You can't even see the love. All you see is darkness. And that's where you stay. Right at deaths door but never actually getting there. Right within arms reach of the light but not being able to find your way back to it.


Until one day, you find a way to pour everything out. You write about it. You speak about it. You cry about it. You spit it all out. You cough it all up. You let everything out. And suddenly you start to feel a little air coming in your lungs again. The light suddenly shines just a little brighter and then even a little brighter until you start to think that maybe... just maybe there may just be some hope yet..."

We pissed off a lot of people and now we need your help!


So we created a submitter's story that made a lot of people angry. It was about the LGBT+ community and the title asked “Is it ok to disagree with the LGBT?” The video then tells the story of a 13 year old Filipino school girl who practically gets bullied for answering “no” when she’s asked by her friend whether she supports the LGBT. You can watch the whole video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lbbOE...


The video actually doesn’t answer the question in the title, but instead it says that bullying is never ok and that we should treat each other with respect, no matter what we believe in. 


As a platform that encourages people to speak up we believe that it’s important to bring our feelings out in the open where we can deal with them properly, even if they are as intolerant as those who don’t support the LGBT+ (Yes MinuteVideos heavily supports the LGBT community and has made several videos to bring awareness to their struggles). We believe that you can’t change someone’s mind if you don’t know what they’re thinking in the first place. That’s why we think it’s better to create safe environments for people to speak their minds where they don’t get bullied for their beliefs. Then we can have healthy discussions that help us learn more about each other and bring us closer together for the right causes.


But even more fundamentally we want to make content that makes the world a better place, and if a video like this doesn’t do that, we’ll delete it. The only problem is, we don’t know what we should do. We believe strongly that this kind of video raises awareness and creates discussions that have the potential to foster understanding. If there’s people out there who feel the same way like the girl in the video then isn’t it better that we talk about it and change their minds rather than forcing them to suppress their feelings? 


But the fact that so many of you have spoken out against this video makes us afraid that we’re doing the wrong thing. And that’s why we’re asking for your help. Do you think that the video is harmful and should be taken down or do you think that it helps to foster meaningful discussion and should stay up despite the people who disagree with it? 


Please let us know what you think in the comments and leave your vote in the poll. We’ll give this poll 48 hours and then do what the majority decides. If more than 50% decide it should be taken down we’ll delete it or else we’ll keep it up. 


With love

𝐌𝐲 𝐒𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐓𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐝 𝐓𝐨 𝐄𝐧𝐝 𝐇𝐞𝐫 𝐎𝐰𝐧 𝐋𝐢𝐟𝐞


"My parents divorced a while back where my brother went to live with my dad and me with my mom. My step-dad previously had a daughter, so when they married, I got a new sister. Growing up with her, I saw her go from a happy teenager to being depressed with occasional suicidal thoughts. I began to notice her eating less and less with some personality changes, but I never thought much of it until the ACCIDENT.

One day, my brother came to visit my mom and me for the week, and we decided to go to the grocery store leaving my step-sister at home alone. When we got back, I was first to unlock the door and heard whimpering and sobbing coming from the bathroom. I didn't know what was going on, all I heard was her voice softly whimpering. My mom and brother were still outside grabbing the groceries from the car so I ran outside sobbing telling them about my sister and how she was crying in the bathroom. As my mom ran inside, my brother explained to me,

"My little sister, please don't freak out! Sister is trying to hurt herself, but we love her, and she will survive."

I ran inside with my brother following my mom and when we opened the door, we saw her with a blade against her wrist about to cut. I looked into her eyes with tears dripping down my face as my mom quickly took the blade away from her and held her down, crying. My brother couldn't handle it and cried while hugging me against his chest, taking me into another room.

My sister now sees a therapist multiple times per week. She is still battling depression but has gotten much better throughout the years. Unfortunately, there have been a few other times when she has tried to harm herself again. I don't view her as my step-sister, but as my true sister and someone, I feel responsible for. After witnessing that event, I never want anyone to ever feel trapped. It may seem like the only option to take the pain away, but when you do that, it hurts those around you so much more. Please, please, don't ever feel like you are alone or that people don't care about you, because we do; including me. Always."

𝐅𝐨𝐜𝐮𝐬 𝐨𝐧 𝐘𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐟 𝐁𝐞𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐎𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐬


"It was my first year of University, I was a straight-A student and there was nothing that could come between me and my dreams. I wanted to become a neurosurgeon and apply for medical school, but it all changed when I met Chris. I don't know what it was about him, but I slowly began to fall for him. He seemed like the perfect guy, smart, nice and funny... all I wanted to do was get to know him. We were assigned as lab partners so I knew this would be my chance, slowly and surely we started talking and learned so much about him in just the first day. We shared so many interests! We both loved 'The Big Bang Theory', had a younger sister and we were very focused on our studies. After two weeks, Chris asked me out to the movies and I said yes without hesitation. While watching the movie, we gazed into each other's eyes and bam! our first kiss happened. As weeks passed by we started officially dating and nothing could break us apart. One year had passed and I thought it was time to introduce Chris to my parents. After having Chris over for dinner I asked my parents what they thought of him. They said he was a nice boy, but didn't want me getting too close to him, I thought this was just them being protective.


Fast forward to 3 years of blissful dating, it had become the day that my acceptance letter from the medical school I applied for would arrive. I WAS ACCEPTED! I ran to Chris and jumped into his arms with joy, I remember he hugged me so tight. We sat down and I continued reading the rest of my letter where we learned I'd be gone for 4 years... I could tell Chris was very upset. After discussing day and night for over two weeks I said to Chris that we needed to talk. I told him that I loved him and that no matter how important medical school is to me, he was more important. He hugged me tight and I held him back but with tears in my eyes. I told my parents and they were so upset... they felt I had lost my purpose in life but I brushed it off because I loved Chris. A few Months later, Christ got an offer from some big hockey school where he would be gone for 2 years. I looked at him and asked if he was going to go and he said yes without any hesitation. We spent the entire day arguing and I explained that I had given up everything for him! I sat in my room crying before I got a text from him saying he wanted to see me right away. I drove over to his house with tears in my eyes and hugged him muttering "I love you". Chris didn't say anything... instead, he said "Actually I called you here to say that we should break up. I just don't feel it anymore, plus this hockey thing is very important for me. I'm sorry, I love you but I choose my dreams". 


Fast forward 5 years: I am happily married to a lovely guy named Brandon and working as a neurosurgeon in a hospital downtown. My husband is an engineer and we're both happy and doing great. I want people to remember to sometimes be selfish, to focus on what's important and good things will find their way to you."

"I am a lesbian. I was dating this girl for about 7 months before my mental health began deteriorating. I started to become more irritable, depressed, and anxious with occasional panic attacks while with her. I eventually went from being a fun-loving outgoing person to a more quiet and reserved person. I let my girlfriend at the time know what was going on with me, but she didn’t seem to understand how dark of a space I was really in. She would yell at me whenever I was down, or she'd accuse me of faking my mental health and even told me I was a piece of trash out of her frustrations and impatience. This cycle went on for over a month until, at one point, I said to myself that if I keep her in my life I’m going to go into an even more downward spiral and my mental health will worsen. So, I told myself that I’d had enough. I was done being treated like a piece of garbage, misunderstood, and pushed down. I texted her and I said, "We have to take a break from each other". Her response was, "Seriously?! You're breaking up with me?! On our anniversary?! I can’t believe you, how could you do this to me?!” She tried calling me and it took every bit of me not to pick up her call, but I remembered my reasoning and declined or ignored her text messages. That following Monday, I finally felt at peace. But our mutual friends kept telling me how I broke her heart and she’s been depressed for days thinking about me. When word got around my school, I was seen as the bad guy and it didn't help that my ex didn’t show up for two days. When she did show up, she'd laugh at me and make snarky comments behind my back. Luckily, I had the support of my friends who actually believed my side of the story and they understand why I needed to break-up with her.

The advice I'd like to give to others going through something similar is, that it’s okay to break-up with someone, especially if you have a valid reason to. Everything will fine and you will grow as a person day-by-day."

16 MILLION SUBSCRIBERS!!!! Thank you all so much ❤️ What video should we make next?

I first started King Kousky on Feb 19, 2014 when I was a freshman in college at Boston University. At the time, my plan was to do gaming videos on King Kousky while uploading Nerf war videos to my other channel, PDK Films. I thought that as I got older I would transition out of making Nerf war videos and into making gaming videos full time.
 
KK as a gaming channel never really took off, as I've never been able to fully dedicate my time to it. I've sporadically uploaded gaming videos here and there, but inevitably I'd stop and go silent on the channel for long periods of time. 

Fast forward to today, Feb 12, 2021, and it has been almost exactly 7 years since conceptualizing and creating King Kousky back in my college dorm. My other channel, PDK Films, is at 15.9 million subscribers (almost 16 million) and growing faster than ever. I never could have imagined that PDK Films would be at where it is today, and after much thought (months and months), I've decided to officially RE-LAUNCH the King Kousky YouTube channel!

Now, over the years when KK was a gaming channel I'd take it seriously for a few months then stop uploading. But this time will be different, and that's because KK isn't going to be a gaming channel. Ultimately, I don't have the passion to run a gaming channel. Sure, I love video games, but it takes a tremendous amount of time, work, and skill to run a successful gaming channel. My passions simply aren't there, but somewhere else: action films and Nerf blasters.

So, you're probably wondering if King Kousky isn't going to be a gaming channel then what is it going to be? My plan for KK is for it to be a live action, scripted 'Nerf war' channel like PDK Films, but I don't want it to be limited to that. PDK Films is a massive channel known as a 'Nerf channel' - it makes Nerf videos and that's it. I want to make any and all kinds of videos on King Kousky, but it will heavily be based around first person shooters and Nerf wars, because that's what I'm passionate about.

That brings the next question: why make Nerf war videos on King Kousky when you already have PDK Films? The answer to that is simple: I have so many ideas and concepts for videos that it just isn't possible to output everything onto one channel without chaos ensuing. Further, the Nerf war videos you're going to see on King Kousky are going to be different: more aggressive, higher production value, and more in sync with what I want to create personally rather than what I want to create to perform well on YouTube.

And don't worry, PDK Films isn't going anywhere! We'll be uploading and staying active on both channels! So, if you haven't already, be sure to subscribe to King Kousky on YouTube so you don't miss our new videos. Right now we're re-uploading some older content on King Kousky for SEO purposes so it might look familiar, but the new original content will start appearing later this year. 

Cheers - Paul
